Preamble: The procedure for the award of cash and appropriation of the prize money to the winning local bodies in the 12 groups of Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan 4.0 has been notified vide Government Decision dated 27.09.2024 at Reference No. Accordingly, a Detailed Project Report of the works to be taken up by the local bodies out of the award amount has been prepared vide Government Decision dated 08.02.2022 at Reference No. Administrative approval has to be obtained from a committee constituted under the chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment and Climate Change.

2. Accordingly, for grant of administrative approval to the Detailed Project Report received from the Awardee Local Bodies, Ms. The Committee has made recommendations after discussing the Detailed Project Report submitted by the Local Bodies in its meetings held on 02.05.2025 under the Chairmanship of Secretary, Department of Environment & Climate Change. Local self-governments concerned as per the recommendations made by the Committee.
The issue of granting administrative approval to the detailed project reports of the institutions was under the consideration of the government.
The government's decision:

The works in the Detailed Project Report costing ₹75,00, 000.00 (Rupees Seventy Five Lakhs only) are being accorded administrative sanction by the Government subject to the following conditions and conditions. The works for which administrative sanction is being granted are shown in the accompanying Annexure-19.
2. Terms and Conditions 1) The operating mechanism for the works in this Detailed Project Report shall be the Mirzagaon Gram Panchayat.

2) The financial and physical progress report of the implementation of the works mentioned in this Detailed Project Report should be sent to my Vasundhara Mission Directorate by the 5th of every month.
3) The implementation of the works in this Detailed Project Report should be completed within the next 6 months from the approval of the Administrator.
4) If the amount of the prize exceeds the amount, it should be made out of self-funding.
5) In case of any increase in the original project cost in this Detailed Project Report for any reason, no additional funds / grants will be made available for the same.

3. Under the Majhi Vasundhara Abhiyan, the Mirzagaon Gram Panchayat has been given a grant of Rs. A prize of ₹1 lakh has been received. Out of the prize money of Rs. Since the detailed project report of the works to be taken out of this prize money has been granted administrative approval by the Government as per paragraph-1 above, the Mirzagaon Gram Panchayat will receive the balance of the prize money of Rs. The Government is approving the disbursement of the second instalment of ₹1 lakh (Rupees thirty-seven lakh fifty thousand only) through Maharashtra Pollution Control Board.
